A ranar Lahadi, Shugaba Donald Trump ya ambaci wata mujallar da ake biyan kuɗi ta China Daily a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register  jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a jihar Iowa, bayan da ya zargi China da tsoma baki a zaben da aka yi a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, wanda China ta musanta.
Kamfanin dillancin labarai na Reuters ya ruwaito cewa jami'an gwamnatin Amurka sun bayyana zargin da Trump ya yi na kokarin da Beijing ke yi na tsoma baki a zaben Amurka a matsayin wani sabon mataki a kokarin da Washington ke karawa na matsa lamba kan kasar Sin.
Ko da yake ya zama ruwan dare ga gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje su yi tallace-tallace don su ƙarfafa cinikayya, Beijing da Washington suna faɗa cikin yaƙin cinikayya da ke ƙaruwa, inda suke cin zarafin juna ta wajen saka haraji a kan kayayyakin da ake shigowa da su.
An ce, takunkumin da China ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya zai shafi masu fitar da kayayyaki a jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, in ji masana na kasar Sin da na Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a kasar Sin kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni illa.
